EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to taxation; removing the prospective expiration
of the Nye County Sales and Use Tax Act of 2007; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes the Board of County Commissioners of Nye County to
2 impose a sales and use tax in Nye County to: (1) recruit, employ and equip
3 additional firefighters, deputy sheriffs to the Sheriff and other public safety
4 personnel; (2) improve and equip existing public safety facilities; and (3) construct
5 and equip new public safety facilities in the areas of Pahrump, Amargosa Valley,
6 Beatty, Tonopah, Round Mountain, Manhattan, Gabbs and any other town or city
7 created in Nye County after October 1, 2007, and in the remaining unincorporated
8 area of Nye County on a pro rata basis. (Nye County Sales and Use Tax Act of
9 2007) The Nye County Sales and Use Tax Act of 2007 is set to expire on
10 October 1, 2027. (Section 23 of chapter 545, Statutes of Nevada 2007, at page
11 3428, as amended by chapter 623, Statutes of Nevada 2019, at page 4192) Sections
12 1 and 2 of this bill remove the prospective expiration of the Act and amendments
13 relating thereto, thereby authorizing the imposition of such a tax in Nye County
14 after October 1, 2027.
